 Career History



Trader

                                    Current                


Merriman Wealth Management LLC


                  Merriman Wealth Management seeks to construct well-balanced and globally-diversified portfolios based on academic research, seeking to provide investors with superior risk-adjusted returns. The firm’s two core investment products, MarketWise and TrendWise primarily use mutual funds and ETFs to help clients achieve their investment goals. The firm's MarketWise strategy is a globally diversified core investment program based on academic research. It relies primarily on low-cost mutual funds and is generally fully invested. Client assets are allocated and rebalanced across a carefully selected mix of mutual funds (typically no-load stock mutual funds managed by DFA). The stock exposure in MarketWise generally includes U.S. and international stock markets (including emerging markets), with small-cap, mid-cap and large-cap funds, as well as U.S. and international real REITs in tax-deferred accounts. Bond allocations generally rely on mutual funds that hold short-term and intermediate-term bonds. In taxable accounts, Merriman seeks greater tax efficiency by relying on municipal bond funds. Merriman's TrendWise is an actively-managed trend-following strategy that applies active risk management techniques to shift investments across asset classes as market conditions change. Portfolios may invest in ETFs, ETNs and mutual funds (excluding DFA funds). These systems are applied to U.S. stocks, international stocks, bonds, REITs and potentially other asset classes such as commodities. Within each asset class, Merriman may invest in multiple funds, each of which employs as independent trend-following timing system. Merriman offers two variations of TrendWise: TrendWise100 and TrendWise80.                





 Other Affiliations




              Gerard Figurelli is affiliated with
                            Merriman Wealth Management LLC.
            





